<hr />

<h2>New Creation Reality</h2>
<p>
When pressure hits, your job is not to panic.
Your job is to stay rooted in Christ:
faith that holds, love that grows, hope that doesn’t fold.
</p>

<p>
God’s justice is not “maybe later.”
It is real, active, and it protects His people in history.
</p>

<hr />

<h2>Reflection</h2>
<p>
Where am I interpreting hardship as abandonment,
instead of seeing it as a place where Christ’s life is proven strong in me?
</p>

